---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
// You'll need to add an image to /public/images/matthew-miller-profile.jpg (or update path)
// Or remove the image section if not desired.
const profileImage = "/images/matthew-miller-profile.jpg"; // **ADD YOUR PROFILE IMAGE HERE**
const newBooksInJewishStudiesLink = "https://newbooksnetwork.com/category/religion-faith/jewish-studies"; // Example, replace with actual
---

<Layout
    title="About Matthew Miller"
    description="Learn more about Matthew Miller, a Principal Analyst in AI, Automation, and Analytics at G2, and a Jewish Studies aficionado with a rich background in technology, research, and content creation."
    image={profileImage}
>
    <main class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 sm:py-16">
        <article class="prose prose-lg lg:prose-xl dark:prose-invert mx-auto">
            <header class="mb-10 not-prose"> {/* not-prose to style h1 differently if needed */}
                <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-primary-light dark:text-primary-dark sm:text-5xl text-center">
                    About Matthew Miller
                </h1>
                {profileImage && (
                    <div class="mt-8 mb-10 flex justify-center">
                        <img
                            src={profileImage}
                            alt="Matthew Miller"
                            width="160"
                            height="160"
                            class="rounded-full shadow-lg aspect-square object-cover"
                            loading="lazy"
                        />
                    </div>
                )}
            </header>

            <p class="lead text-xl sm:text-2xl text-center !mb-10 text-secondary-light dark:text-secondary-dark">
                An accomplished Principal Analyst in AI, Automation, and Analytics at G2, and a Jewish Studies aficionado.
                Matthew brings a unique blend of technical expertise, research acumen, and a deep appreciation for Jewish thought and culture.
            </p>

            <h2>Tech Prowess</h2>
            <p>
                Matthew Miller is an accomplished Principal Analyst in AI, Automation, and Analytics at G2 with a strong background in technology and research. He has extensive experience as an analyst and thought leader having worked in various industries across the United States, Canada, and the United Kingdom.
            </p>
            <p>
                A proud McGill University and Queen Mary University of London (QMUL) alumnus, Matthew specializes in AI, machine learning, natural language processing, AI ethics, and facial recognition. His expertise has led him to co-found VAICE, a non-profit voice tech consultancy, and work with numerous organizations such as CognitionX and Bitext.
            </p>
            <p>
                Matthew is a skilled writer and content creator, having contributed to numerous publications and daily newsletters. He is known for his research and analysis on AI-related topics and has written on subjects like stream analytics, COVID-19's impact on data professionals, and synthetic data generation.
            </p>
            <p>
                Based in the Greater Chicago Area, Matthew is a well-connected professional with over 4,000 followers on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/matthewemir/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a> and is always eager to discuss AI, ML, NLP, AI ethics, and facial recognition.
            </p>

            <h2>Jewish Studies Journey</h2>
            <p>
                Beyond the world of technology, Matthew is also a Jewish studies aficionado. He pursued his passion for Jewish Studies for his BA at McGill University, learning under the guidance of esteemed scholars such as Professor Lawrence Kaplan and Professor B. Barry Levy.
            </p>
            <p>
                He actively contributes to the field as a host of the <a href={newBooksInJewishStudiesLink} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">New Books in Jewish Studies podcast</a> â€“ check out his insightful interviews.
            </p>
            <p>
                Matthew is privileged to collaborate with fabulous Jewish organizations and individuals, including The Habura and Rabbi Efrem Goldberg, on content creation and social media management, helping to share valuable Jewish wisdom and insights with a wider audience.
            </p>
        </article>
    </main>
</Layout>